-- make a function to rename moves easier
local function setmovename(move, name)
    local hotbar = plrgui:WaitForChild("Hotbar") -- get the hotbar gui
    local backpack = hotbar and hotbar:FindFirstChild("Backpack") -- if hotbar exists get the backpack
    local hotbarf = backpack and backpack:FindFirstChild("Hotbar") -- if the backpack exists get the hotbar FRAME

    local tool = hotbarf:FindFirstChild(tostring(move)) -- get the move's button (not really a button)
    local base = tool and tool:WaitForChild("Base") -- if the move exists, get it's button (base)
    local toolname = base and base:WaitForChild("ToolName") -- if the button exists, get the move's name
    if toolname then -- if the move's name  exists, set the name
        toolname.Text = name
    end
end

end

-- set ultimate name
local function setultname()
    local gui = plrgui:WaitForChild("ScreenGui") -- gets the player's gui object
    if gui then -- if the gui exists, get ultimate bar
        local magichp = gui:FindFirstChild("MagicHealth")
        if magichp then -- if the ultimate bar exists, get the ultimate text
            local textlabel = magichp:FindFirstChild("TextLabel")
            if textlabel  -- if the ult text exists, get the background font thingy
                local bglabel = textlabel:FindFirstChild("TextLabel")
                if bglabel or textlabel then -- if either exists set ONLY the front text's text
                    local name = "MEGAPHONE"
                    textlabel.Text = name
                    if bglabel then -- if the background text exists, also set it's text
                        bglabel.Text = name
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

-- on ultimate
local function onult(track)

    -- getting character and humanoid
    local char = lplr.Character or lplr.CharacterAdded:Wait()
    local hum = char and char:FindFirstChild("Humanoid")

    -- saving the original walk speed and jump power
    local ogjump = hum.JumpPower
    local ogws = hum.WalkSpeed

    -- making player unable to walk nor jump
    hum.JumpPower = 0
    hum.WalkSpeed = 0

    wait(track.Length + 0.1) -- wait until ultimate animation is finished

    -- set ultimate move names
    setultmoves()

    -- reset walk speed and jump power
    hum.JumpPower = ogjump
    hum.WalkSpeed = ogws

end

local function playspeakvfx()
    local char = plr.Character or plr.CharacterAdded:Wait()
    local head = char:FindFirstChild("Head")
    if head then
        local emitter = Instance.new("ParticleEmitter")
        emitter.Enabled = false

        emitter.LightEmission = 0.5
        emitter.LightInfluence = 0
        emitter.Orientation = Enum.ParticleOrientation.VelocityPerpendicular
        emitter.Size = NumberSequence.new(1, 3)
        emitter.Texture = "rbxassetid://9573351641"
        emitter.Transparency = NumberSequence.new(0.3, 1)
        emitter.Lifetime = 1
        emitter.Rate = 30
        emitter.Speed = 2.5

        emitter.Parent = head
        emitter:Emit(5)

        Debris:AddItem(emitter, 10)
    end
end

-- stop current animations to support playanimation()
local function stopcurrentanims()
    -- getting character and humanoid
    local char = lplr.Character or lplr.CharacterAdded:Wait()
    local hum = char:FindFirstChild("Humanoid")
    -- for each animation playing, stop the animation
    for _, v in pairs(hum:GetPlayingAnimationTracks()) do
        v:Stop()
    end
end

local function playanimation(id, details)
    -- stopping anims for the new anim to play smoothly
    stopcurrentanims()

    -- getting character and humanoid
    local char = lplr.Character or lplr.CharacterAdded:Wait()
    local hum = char:FindFirstChild("Humanoid")

    -- making anim
    local anim = Instance.new("Animation")
    anim.AnimationId = "rbxassetid://" .. id

    -- making anim track
    local track = hum:LoadAnimation(anim)

    -- ensuring anim details
    local starttime = details.starttime or 0
    local delay = details.delay or 0
    local speed = details.speed or 1
    local looped = details.looped or false

    -- setting details
    track.Looped = looped
    if delay > 0 then
        task.delay(delay, function()
            track:Play()
        end)
    else
        track:Play()
    end
    
    -- anim final touches
    track:AdjustSpeed(speed)
    track.TimePosition = starttime

    -- finishing up
    game.Debris:AddItem(anim, 1)
    return track
end

-- hooking anims to character
local char = lplr.Character or lplr.CharacterAdded:Wait()
local hum = char:FindFirstChild("Humanoid")
-- base moveset and ult moveset
hum.AnimationPlayed:Connect(function(track)
    -- base
    for _, v in ipairs(animations) do
        if track.Animation.AnimationId == "rbxassetid://" .. v.id then
            local newtrack = playanimation(v.newid, v.animdetails)
            if v.move and type(v.move) == "number" then
                loadstring("mv" .. tostring(v.move) .. "()")()
            elseif type(v.move) == "string" and v.move == "ult" then
                onult(newtrack)
            end
        end
    end

    -- ult
    for _, v in ipairs(ultanims) do
        if track.Animation.AnimationId == "rbxassetid://" .. v.id then
            playanimation(v.newid, v.animdetails)
            if type(v.move) == "string" then
                loadstring(tostring(v.move)"(newtrack)")()
            end
        end
    end
end)

hum.AnimationPlayed:Connect(function(track)
    for _, v in ipairs(punchanims) do
        if track.Animation.AnimationId == "rbxassetid://" .. v.id then
            playanimation(v.newid, v.animdetails)
            playm1vfx(char)
        end
    end
end)
